{{/* WHY: "Your job" bullets carry the executor contract: DeclaredOutputPaths write-scoping (in-pod harness enforces), run tests/lints, commit in worktree only, and no-push (pods have no git credentials). All four directives steer the model's actions throughout the task. */ -}}
Your job:
  - Read the per-Task instructions at /workspace/envelopes/{{.TaskUID}}/in.json.
  - Operate inside the worktree at /workspace/worktrees/{{.TaskUID}}/. Stay
    inside DeclaredOutputPaths from the envelope — writes outside that set
    are rejected by the in-pod harness.
  - Run tests / lints / build steps as needed; let the harness enforce
    wall-clock and iteration caps.
  - Commit your work inside the per-Task worktree. The orchestrator's
    push Job will fast-forward the per-run branch — do not push from this
    pod. Subagent pods have no git credentials.

{{/* WHY: EnvelopeOut fields (result/usage/git.headSHA/artifacts) are parsed by the orchestrator to advance task status; all four are required for a valid completion record. */ -}}
Emit your output as an EnvelopeOut with:
  - result: a one-line summary of the task outcome.
  - usage:  the token/cost/iteration tally (the harness aggregates this).
  - git.headSHA: the SHA your final commit produced in the worktree.
  - artifacts: the set of paths you wrote, scoped to DeclaredOutputPaths.

